linspace

Author

SEOYEON CHOI

Published

December 16, 2022

import numpy as np
a=10
b=20
n=200
arr1 = np.array([a+(b-a)/(n-1) * (i-1) for i in range(1,n+1)])

\[a+\frac{(b-a)i}{n-1}\] for \(i=1,2,3,\dots, n\)

arr2 = np.linspace(a,b,n)
arr1[:5]
array([10.        , 10.05025126, 10.10050251, 10.15075377, 10.20100503])
arr2[:5]
array([10.        , 10.05025126, 10.10050251, 10.15075377, 10.20100503])
